  "text": "The present study aimed to compare the efficacy of two dysphagia interventions developed to strengthen the suprahyoid muscles. A total of 23 healthy older adults were randomized to one of the two therapy groups: the HLE and the NMES for a 2-week period. The two groups were compared on the electromyographic features of the supra-and infrahyoid muscles during swallowing. Pain and discomfort was reported by the majority of subjects who performed the HLE, whilst a few subjects in the NMES group reported a few mild complications. Furthermore, in the HLE group one person withdrew from the therapy due to severe neck pain. These findings are in agreement with studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] reporting that completing the HLE period is difficult for patients and even for healthy older adults and warning that these difficulties may reduce the clinical feasibility of the HLE.",
